				<p>
					If we divide <m>\frac{1}{5}</m> in half and <m>\frac{1}{2}</m> into five pieces, we find that <m>\frac{1}{10}</m> goes into both <m>\frac{1}{5}</m> and <m>\frac{1}{2}</m> evenly.
				</p>


<figure xml:id="addfracs2">
	<image>
	<latex-image>
	\begin{tikzpicture}
		\draw[ultra thick,green][|-] (-5,.5) -- (-4.5,.5);
